net.sf.jclec.mo.command

Class NonDominatedFeasibleSolutionsExtractor

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.jclec.mo.command.Command
      • net.sf.jclec.mo.command.NonDominatedSolutionsExtractor
        • net.sf.jclec.mo.command.NonDominatedFeasibleSolutionsExtractor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, net.sf.jclec.IConfigure, net.sf.jclec.JCLEC

    public class NonDominatedFeasibleSolutionsExtractor
extends NonDominatedSolutionsExtractor
    This command extracts the non-dominated solutions of the given population considering that the population can contain both feasible and infeasible solutions. It requires the definition of the dominance principle to be used. Here, any comparator extending from ParetoComparator can be used. Infeasible solutions will be discarded before comparing the dominance criterion, so individuals should implement the IConstrained interface. The given population is not modified during the execution of the command, since the set of non-dominated solutions is stored in a specific list that can be retrieved using the getNonDominatedSolutions method.

    HISTORY:

    • (AR|JRR|SV, 1.0, March 2018) First release.
